sentences: Madi Diaz (born May 14, 1986) is an American singer-songwriter and musician.
She was featured in Rock School, director Don Argott's 2005 documentary about the program as Madi Diaz-Svalgard.
The self-released album Skin And Bones (2007) was the result, and a songwriting and performing partnership between Diaz and Ryan stuck.
In 2008, Diaz and Ryan continued writing and began playing shows in New York City.
She was featured in Paste magazine as one of the "Top Ten Buzziest Acts" at SXSW 2009, and had songs featured on cw
Her EP, Far from the Things That We Know, was released on September 20, 2011, by TinyOGRE Entertainment.
The EP previewed songs from her full-length album, Plastic Moon, which was released in January 2012.
In February 2012, Diaz moved to Los Angeles, marking a new chapter in her music career.
Now working solo, her next album, We Threw Our Hearts in the Fire, was released on October 23, 2012.
She released the single "Stay Together" on July 11, 2014.
It is the first single off of her album, Phantom, which was released in September 2014.
On February 11, 2021, ANTI- Records announced that Diaz had signed with them, alongside the release of her first single with the label titled "Man In Me".
